<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Mamba&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Overview">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Overview">Overview</span></h2>
<p>The <b>Mamba</b> is a very fast <a href="/index.php/M3" title="M3">M3</a>, but is also very lightly shielded, meaning that it will not last long in a fight with another ship of its class.  However, it is not to be taken lightly due to its agility. It is very capable when used as a heavy interceptor for chasing down smaller fighters.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Mamba&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Background">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Background">Background</span></h2>
<p>A long-serving and deadly fighter developed by the <a href="/index.php/Split" title="Split">Split</a> Military. It has been only in recent years that this ship has been made available to the public. The current Split Patriarch has a small fleet of these ships that act as escort ships that accompany the primary destroyer of the fleet. In the hands of an experience pilot, this ship can survive the darkest of battles, due to the ship's high speed it can avoid most of laser beams and missiles.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Mamba&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Physical Characteristics">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Physical_Characteristics">Physical Characteristics</span></h2>
<p>The Mamba shares its triangular, dagger-shaped fuselage and short, pointed wings with the other Split fighters.  Like all Split vessels, it is painted a rusty red color.
</p><p>In many ways the development of the Mamba heralded the design of the <a href="/index.php/M4%2B" title="M4+">M4+</a>. However, as an M3, the Mamba features a more powerful weapons generator, wider weapons compatibility and a larger weapons capacity.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Mamba&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Variants">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Variants">Variants</span></h2>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Mamba&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Mamba">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Mamba">Mamba</span></h3>
<p>Not featuring any fancy title, the basic version of the ship is the standard by which other variants are measured.
</p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Mamba&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Advanced Mamba">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Advanced_Mamba">Advanced Mamba</span></h3>
<p>Advanced variants of ships are rare, and usually possess equal or improved stats in every area over their regular versions.
</p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Mamba&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Mamba Raider">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Mamba_Raider">Mamba Raider</span></h3>
<p>Raider variants are faster and usually have a higher shield generator power than their regular counterparts, but trade off cargo capacity and some have reduced shield capacity despite the more powerful generator.
</p><p>The Mamba Raider is often regarded as the deadliest version.
</p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Mamba&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Mamba Sentinel">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Mamba_Sentinel">Mamba Sentinel</span></h3>
<p>Sentinel variants of ships tend to be slower, but with higher total shield capacity. Sometimes the shield class is also upgraded for instance from 25 MJ to 200 MJ.
</p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Mamba&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Mamba Vanguard">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Mamba_Vanguard">Mamba Vanguard</span></h3>
<p>Vanguard variants of ships are slightly faster and have bigger weapons generators than their regular counterparts.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Mamba&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Combat">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Combat"> Combat </span></h2>
<p>Fighting in the Mamba requires careful attention given to evasion, as the ship will not survive long if caught in a volley of fire. Strafing tactics are often employed by Mamba pilots; shoot until the target shoots back, break off and evade until you get out of range, turn around and repeat.
</p><p>Absence of a rear turret makes several Mamba variants vulnerable to missiles. Relatively light shielding puts it at risk against weapons fire it can't evade effectively, like flak bursts or kyon weaponry. 
</p>
