<p>A standard Mamba is also available as an <a href="/index.php/Ownerless_ships" title="Ownerless ships">ownerless vessel</a>.
</p><p>The Advanced Mamba is granted as a corporate reward by the <a href="/index.php/Strong_Arms" title="Strong Arms">Strong Arms</a> upon reaching <a href="/index.php/Reputation#Strong_Arms" title="Reputation">level 7</a>.
</p><p>The Mamba Sentinel is not in production and must be <a href="/index.php/Bail" title="Bail">captured</a>.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Mamba&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: Suggested Roles">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Suggested_Roles"> Suggested Roles</span></h2>
<p>A very powerful M3, the Mamba's usefulness comes into its own as a player ship, particularly the Advanced Mamba. With high speed and a large weapon generator, the Mamba is extremely good at not getting hit. This speed makes it an ideal mercenary's ship. It also has a surprisingly large cargobay, so can carry a reasonable amount of missiles or jump fuel.
</p><p>While it can be a good fighter to use on carriers, its lack of shielding compared to most other M3s means they may need replacing relatively often.
</p>
